name: Brews Brothers Coffee
directions: Left of the ordering counter
comment: If you would like to use this restroom, I would buy something, I didn't check if the restroom is only for paying customers, but it's just not cool to use the restroom at a small businesses and not get something. The restroom is in very good condition and is not one of those nasty truck stop bathrooms. Lastly, I'm not trans, but am LGBT, and I like helping out my trans buddies!

name: Beverly Hills High School
directions: First floor of main building (not the science building) , next to stairwell that leads to library. It's in a little corner adjacent to where the old theater was.
comment: As this is in a high school, you can use this restroom if you aren't attending BHHS, but it's better if you're a student. They also lock it after 4:00 PM everyday, just like all the other restrooms. Oh, side note, if you go to this school and you're trans, I'm starting a GSA club 2017-2018 year, and it'd be awesome of you to join! - Harrison

name: Gralehaus
directions: In the back by the door to the garden seating area. There is a sign marked "toiletten".
comment: It is a restaurant sort of place, so it would be polite to order something, I think. Though I'm sure they wouldn't refuse you access to the bathroom. They have good coffee and some sodas and drinks, for a small thing to buy (excellent food, if you end up staying longer). The aesthetic is hipster, but there's some queer undertones so you should be welcome.
